<home-ribbon>KnolBase</home-ribbon>

<home-section>

<p>KnolBase is a federated knownledge that contains approximately two billion
facts about 100 million entities.<p>

<p>Every day a new knowledge base is built from a Wikidata live-feed as well as
a number of other information sources:</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="/kb/Q52">Wikipedia</a> (aliases, infoboxes, summaries, categories, popularity, 30 languages)</li>
<li><a href="/kb/Q795419">CVR</a> (Danish Central Business Register)</a></li>
<li><a href="/kb/">Reddit</a> (celebrities and photos)</a></li>
<li><a href="/kb/Q918">Twitter</a> (photos)</a></li>
<li><a href="/kb/Q37312">IMDB</a> (photos)</a></li>
<li><a href="/kb/Q55259097">Global LEI index</a> (companies)</a></li>
<li><a href="/kb/Q90405608">FactGrid</a> (historic research database)</a></li>
</ul>

<h3>W3C Reconcialition Service API</h3>

<p>KnolBase has a W3C Reconcialition Service API so it can be used as a
reconciliation service for <a href="https://openrefine.org/">OpenRefine</a> by
specifying <a href="https://ringgaard.com/reconcile/">https://ringgaard.com/reconcile/</a>
as the service endpoint.</p>

